Thank you Adriene! My daughter and I have been doing this 30 day class.  We are so delighted! This is her 2nd time doing it, my first time ever doing Yoga.  I am 55 yrs old and have been suffering from stiff joints for years.  I must now say, doing this 10 days have made me more flexible and the aches are almost nonexistent...well other than aches from core, butt and other muscles I have not used in decades probably.  I was recently walking 7 miles a day, 5-6 days a week but my poor feet were crying. I decreased the amount to 3-4 miles 4-5 days a week...now that I have implemented Yoga.  What a difference today makes say my feet and all of me. Lol.  This day was rather challenging for me though.  This morning as I got up at 5:30A to walk the dog a family of 6 raccoons were outside. They were looking at us like they were going to attack...made a loud almost pigeon sound...2 were heading towards us, I ran into the garage and somehow jammed my toe on the car tire.  It hurts but I was determined to do the class so I did what I could without adding more pain to it.  I am so grateful to God for you and my daughter.  Yoga is changing my life for best!!! You Rock and I love your sweet spirit Adriene. Thank you, thank you, thank you!!

THANK YOU! I finally know what it means to ground into all four corners of the feet. I could never figure out where the "corners" of my feet were. I was lifting my toes as a check when we do balancing poses but when you said "the ball joint of the big toe and the ball joint of the pinky toe" for the front corners I got it. I feel the ball joint of my big toes all the time very easily, but I had to reach down, put my finger under my foot and feel to find the ball joint of my pinky toe. That did it and I pushed into it and found my foot and legs rotate to line up just right. Turns out my archers roll in naturally, so this reaally helped me find an alignment from toe to thigh that I didn't even know I was supposed to have.
